The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks (NN) in highly-automated driving functionality, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus of the paper is on identifying best safety engineering practices for NN and other learning-enabled components, which suggests a software engineering (cs.SE) perspective. The proposed metrics for measuring NN dependability attributes, such as robustness, interpretability, completeness, and correctness, indicate a focus on security and privacy (cs.CR) as well as control systems (cs.SY).
